        <num>CCRP 219</num>
        <heading>219.  Officer may summon assistance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 219.  Officer may summon assistance
A peace officer making a lawful arrest may call upon as many persons as he considers necessary to aid him in making the arrest.  A person thus called upon shall be considered a peace officer for such purposes.</p>
        </content>
